                                <condition>The inscription is incomplete as the other angle bearing the latter portion of the inscription has been split off from the stone. What remains of the inscription is much worn and damaged, the <q>first Q is flaked, and the C is practically worn away</q> (Macalister 1945, 52). Macalister (1897, 77) notes that nothing definite can be stated about the inscription after it turns onto the top of the stone. </condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>The inscription reads up the dexter angle of the main face of the stone and continues across the top of the stone (Macalister 1945, 52).</layout>
